# Sarcos Technology and Robotics Corporation
**Category:** ventures
**Domain:** robotics / industrial automation
**Website:** https://www.sarcos.com

## Overview
Sarcos Technology and Robotics Corporation designs, develops, and manufactures robotic systems for industrial, defense, and commercial applications. Its product line includes the Guardian™ XO full-body powered exoskeleton, which enables workers to lift heavy loads with reduced strain, and the Guardian™ XT mobile robot for remote manipulation in hazardous environments. The company also offers teleoperation and autonomy software to enhance robotic capabilities.

Sarcos was founded in 1983 by Dr. Stephen Jacobsen, a professor at the University of Utah, and originally focused on defense and aerospace robotics. The company went public in 2021 through a merger with Rotor Acquisition Corp., a special purpose acquisition company (SPAC). Sarcos has since expanded its focus to include industrial workforce augmentation and logistics automation.

## Utah connection
Sarcos was founded in Salt Lake City, Utah, and maintains its headquarters there. The company has deep roots in the state’s engineering and robotics community, leveraging talent from the University of Utah and local tech ecosystem. Utah’s strong manufacturing base and supportive business climate have contributed to Sarcos’ growth. The company is a key player in Utah’s emerging robotics and automation cluster.

